{panel:title=2019.10.04 Status update}
As outlined in the [Java 11 and OpenJDK support for Atlassian Server and Data Center |https://community.atlassian.com/t5/Jira-discussions/Java-11-and-OpenJDK-support-for-Atlassian-Server-amp-Data-Center/m-p/872998#M4575] post, all BTF products will be compatible with Java 11.

Note that Oracle's standard support for Java 8 ends in January, 2019; it's also possible to purchase extended support from Oracle. The [Adopt OpenJDK|https://adoptopenjdk.net/] project supports Java 8 till 2026. You can run Fisheye and Crucible on Adopt OpenJDK as well.

At the moment, we plan to release Fisheye and Crucible compatible with Java 11 no sooner than end of 2020.
{panel}

---

{panel:title=2020.11.30 Status update}
As the [Adopt OpenJDK|https://adoptopenjdk.net/] project supports Java 8 till 2026, we expect to add support for Java 11 in Fisheye and Crucible in 2022.
{panel}

